# vtms-sdr

RTL-SDR audio recorder, frequency scanner, and live monitor for VHF/UHF radio communications.

`vtms-sdr` turns a cheap RTL-SDR USB dongle into a command-line radio tool. Record audio from any frequency in the 24 MHz -- 1.766 GHz range with FM, AM, or SSB demodulation, scan bands for active or unused channels, transcribe voice communications in real time with Whisper AI, and monitor audio live through your speakers with a terminal UI.

## Requirements

### System dependencies

| Package | Required for | Install (Fedora) | Install (Debian/Ubuntu) |
|---------|-------------|-------------------|------------------------|
| `librtlsdr` | All SDR operations | `dnf install rtl-sdr` | `apt install librtlsdr-dev` |
| `ffmpeg` | MP3 output only | `dnf install ffmpeg` | `apt install ffmpeg` |
| `portaudio` | Live audio monitor | `dnf install portaudio-devel` | `apt install libportaudio2` |

### Python

Python 3.10 or newer.

## Installation

```bash
# Clone and install
git clone https://github.com/jeefy/vtms-sdr.git
cd vtms-sdr

# Create a virtual environment (recommended)
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate

# Install core package
pip install -e .

# Install with live transcription support
pip install -e ".[transcribe]"

# Install with live audio monitoring
pip install -e ".[monitor]"

# Install everything (transcription + monitoring + dev tools)
pip install -e ".[transcribe,monitor,dev]"
```

## Quick start

```bash
# Record FM audio from a frequency for 30 seconds
vtms-sdr record -f 146.52M -m fm -d 30

# Scan the 2-meter ham band for active frequencies
vtms-sdr scan active --start 144M --end 148M --step 25k

# Transcribe a previously recorded file
vtms-sdr transcribe recording.wav
```

## Commands

### `vtms-sdr record` -- Record audio

Records demodulated audio from a single frequency to a WAV or MP3 file. Press `Ctrl+C` to stop gracefully (partial recordings are preserved).

```bash
# Basic FM recording (auto-generated filename, records until Ctrl+C)
vtms-sdr record -f 146.52M -m fm

# Record GMRS channel to a named file for 60 seconds
vtms-sdr record -f 462.5625M -m fm -o gmrs.wav -d 60

# Record SSB (sideband) with squelch disabled
vtms-sdr record -f 7.2M -m ssb --squelch -100

# Record to MP3 format
vtms-sdr record -f 462.5625M -m fm --format mp3 -o channel.mp3

# Set manual gain (dB) instead of automatic
vtms-sdr record -f 146.52M -m fm -g 40

# Use a preset profile (see Presets section below)
vtms-sdr record --preset nascar --preset-file presets.yaml

# Record with live speech-to-text transcription
vtms-sdr record -f 146.52M -m fm --transcribe --model base \
    --transcript comms.log --label PIT-CREW

# Record with live audio monitoring (plays through speakers)
vtms-sdr record -f 146.52M -m fm --monitor --volume 0.8
```

**Options:**

| Flag | Description | Default |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `-f, --freq` | Frequency (e.g. `146.52M`, `7200k`, `462.5625M`) | required* |
| `-m, --mod` | Modulation: `fm`, `am`, `ssb` | `fm` |
| `-o, --output` | Output filename | auto-generated |
| `--format` | Output format: `wav`, `mp3` | `wav` |
| `-d, --duration` | Duration in seconds | until Ctrl+C |
| `-g, --gain` | SDR gain in dB or `auto` | `auto` |
| `--squelch` | Squelch threshold in dB | `-40` |
| `--device` | RTL-SDR device index | `0` |
| `--transcribe` | Enable live transcription | off |
| `--model` | Whisper model: `auto`, `tiny`, `base`, `small`, `medium`, `large` | `auto` |
| `--transcript` | Transcript output file | stdout |
| `--label` | Channel label for transcripts | none |
| `--preset` | Named preset from YAML file | none |
| `--preset-file` | Path to preset YAML file | auto-discovered |
| `--monitor` | Enable live audio + terminal UI | off |
| `--volume` | Initial monitor volume (0.0 -- 1.0) | `0.5` |

*Not required when using `--preset`.

### `vtms-sdr scan active` -- Find active frequencies

Performs a single sweep across a frequency range and reports channels where signal power exceeds a threshold.

```bash
# Scan the 2-meter ham band
vtms-sdr scan active --start 144M --end 148M --step 25k

# Scan GMRS band with a stricter threshold, save results to CSV
vtms-sdr scan active --start 462M --end 467M --step 12.5k \
    --threshold -30 -o scan.csv

# Scan UHF with manual gain
vtms-sdr scan active --start 440M --end 450M --step 25k -g 40
```

**Options:**

| Flag | Description | Default |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `--start` | Start frequency | required |
| `--end` | End frequency | required |
| `--step` | Step size (e.g. `25k`, `12.5k`) | required |
| `--threshold` | Detection threshold in dB | `-30` |
| `-o, --output` | Save results to CSV file | stdout only |
| `--device` | RTL-SDR device index | `0` |
| `-g, --gain` | SDR gain in dB or `auto` | `auto` |

### `vtms-sdr scan clear` -- Find unused frequencies

Monitors a frequency range over time and reports channels that remain clear (below threshold) for the entire monitoring period. Useful for finding open frequencies to use.

```bash
# Monitor 2-meter band for 5 minutes
vtms-sdr scan clear --start 144M --end 148M --step 25k -d 300

# Monitor GMRS band for 10 minutes
vtms-sdr scan clear --start 462M --end 467M --step 12.5k -d 600

# Quick 60-second scan with CSV output
vtms-sdr scan clear --start 440M --end 445M --step 25k -d 60 -o clear.csv
```

**Options:** Same as `scan active`, plus:

| Flag | Description | Default |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `-d, --duration` | Monitoring duration in seconds | `300` |

### `vtms-sdr transcribe` -- Transcribe audio files

Transcribe a previously recorded audio file using Whisper AI. Requires the `[transcribe]` extra (`pip install -e ".[transcribe]"`).

```bash
# Basic transcription (prints to stdout)
vtms-sdr transcribe recording.wav

# Use a specific model and save to a file
vtms-sdr transcribe recording.wav --model base -o transcript.log

# Add a channel label to each line
vtms-sdr transcribe recording.wav --label PIT-CREW -o transcript.log
```

**Options:**

| Flag | Description | Default |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `FILE` | Audio file path (positional) | required |
| `--model` | Whisper model size | `auto` |
| `-o, --output` | Transcript output file | stdout |
| `--label` | Channel label prefix | none |

## Presets

Presets let you save frequently-used frequency configurations in a YAML file instead of typing all the flags every time.

### Preset file format

Create a file named `presets.yaml` (or `vtms-sdr.yaml`) in your working directory:

```yaml
presets:
  nascar:
    freq: "462.5625M"
    mod: fm
    gain: 40
    squelch: -35
    label: "SPOTTER"

  pit-crew:
    freq: "464.500M"
    mod: fm
    squelch: -30
    label: "PIT"

  two-meter:
    freq: "146.52M"
    mod: fm

  marine-ch16:
    freq: "156.8M"
    mod: fm
    squelch: -35
    label: "MARINE-16"
```

Each preset must have at least a `freq` field. All other fields are optional and correspond to `record` command flags.

### Using presets

```bash
# Auto-discover presets.yaml in current directory
vtms-sdr record --preset nascar

# Specify a preset file explicitly
vtms-sdr record --preset pit-crew --preset-file /path/to/presets.yaml

# Override preset values with flags
vtms-sdr record --preset nascar -d 120 --monitor
```

## Frequency format

Frequencies can be specified with unit suffixes:

| Input | Interpreted as |
|-------|---------------|
| `146.52M` or `146.52MHz` | 146,520,000 Hz |
| `7200k` or `7200kHz` | 7,200,000 Hz |
| `1.42G` or `1.42GHz` | 1,420,000,000 Hz |
| `462562500` | 462,562,500 Hz (raw Hz) |

The RTL-SDR supports frequencies from **24 MHz to 1.766 GHz**.

## Architecture

```
RTL-SDR dongle
  --> SDRDevice.stream()          IQ samples at 2.4 Msps
  --> Demodulator.demodulate()    Audio at 48 kHz (FM/AM/SSB)
  --> AudioRecorder               Squelch-gated WAV/MP3 writing
      --> Transcriber              Live speech-to-text (optional)
      --> AudioMonitor.feed()      Live speaker output (optional)
```

### Modules

| Module | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `cli.py` | Click-based CLI entry point and command definitions |
| `sdr.py` | RTL-SDR device wrapper with context-manager lifecycle |
| `demod.py` | FM, AM, and SSB demodulators (factory pattern) |
| `recorder.py` | Audio writer with squelch gating and SIGINT handling |
| `scanner.py` | Active and clear frequency scanning with FFT power measurement |
| `monitor.py` | Live audio playback and curses terminal UI |
| `transcriber.py` | Whisper-based speech-to-text (live and file modes) |
| `presets.py` | YAML preset file loading and validation |
| `utils.py` | Frequency parsing, dB conversion, helpers |

## Development

```bash
# Install with dev dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev,transcribe,monitor]"

# Run the test suite
pytest

# Run with coverage
pytest --cov

# Lint (if ruff is installed)
ruff check src/ tests/
```

Tests are fully mocked and do not require an RTL-SDR dongle.

